Bob Kuwahara was an expat Japanese animator who worked at Terrytoons (the guys who created Mighty Mouse, got Ralph Bakshi on the ground and probably made more than a few boomers into furries) and was known for his preference to anthropomorphic designs even outside the confines of the studio. He co-produced a series called Hashimoto-san about a Japanese mouse living in 'Merica with his wife and two kids, which if you're familiar with at all, would probably make you think some racist American drummed it up what with how stereotypical the cartoon could be at times.

Hashimoto had a cute wife though, Hanako, and seeing as I sincerely expect Paramount to sooner let the old cells and all other references to these cartoons rot in a file cabinet somewhere than restoring and rereleasing them for modern viewing, it can be safely stated that Hanako is probably doomed to eternal anthro obscurity.

But here's a cute fridge magnet I found of her that's older than my dad. So that's cool.
